headlines.description: — LaMelo Ball returned from a 21-game absence with 11 points, leading the Charlotte Hornets to a 107-94 victory over the Detroit Pistons on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: LaMelo Ball returns, helps Hornets beat Pistons 107-94

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Houston Rockets

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry bounced back from a rough first half with 23 of his 30 points in the third quarter, and the Golden State Warriors beat the Houston Rockets 113-87 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Curry's big 3rd quarter leads Warriors past Rockets, 113-87

headlines.description: — Trae Young scored 33 points, Clint Capela had 20 points and 11 rebounds and the Atlanta Hawks snapped a three-game slide with a 108-97 victory over the undermanned Chicago Bulls on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Young scores 33, Capela has double-double, Hawks beat Bulls

headlines.description: — Kendrick Nunn scored 22 points and Duncan Robinson had 20, helping the Miami Heat move into a tie for sixth place in the Eastern Conference with a 124-107 victory over the Cleveland Cavaliers on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nunn scores 22 points, Heat beat Cavaliers 124-107

headlines.description: — Cole Anthony made a 3-pointer with 0.1 seconds remaining, giving him a career-best 26 points and the Orlando Magic a 112-111 victory over the Memphis Grizzlies on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Anthony's 3-pointer gives Magic 112-111 win over Grizzlies

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Minnesota Timberwolves

headlines.description: — Zion Williamson scored nine of his 37 points in overtime and the New Orleans Pelicans came back to beat the Minnesota Timberwolves 140-136 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Williamson scores 37; Pelicans beat Wolves 140-136 in OT

events.name: Indiana Pacers at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Domantas Sabonis had a triple-double in the first half and the Indiana Pacers flirted with the most lopsided victory in NBA history before beating the Oklahoma City Thunder 152-95 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sabonis has triple-double by half; Pacers top Thunder 152-95

headlines.description: — Dorian Finney-Smith hit a go-ahead 3-pointer in the final seconds, Luka Doncic ended his longest stretch without a triple-double since his rookie season and the Dallas Mavericks won a 125-124 thriller over the Washington Wizards on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic, Mavericks win 125-124 thriller over surging Wizards

headlines.description: — Bojan Bogdanovic scored 34 points — including six 3-pointers — to lead the Utah Jazz to a 106-102 victory over the Toronto Raptors on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bogdanovic scores 34 as Jazz rally to beat Raptors 106-102

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic had 30 points and 14 rebounds, Michael Porter Jr. scored 25 points and the Denver Nuggets moved past the Los Angeles Clippers for the third seed in the Western Conference with a 110-104 victory Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Denver moves into 3rd in West with 110-104 win over Clippers
